metadata.name: Fractal in the words #495
metadata.description:
Tribute to Herbert W. Franke.

Fractal based on mathematics is placed in Japanese words.

Color Pallet has 10 variations.
Draw Color has 2 variations.
Background Color has 4 variations.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
- Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
- Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4000 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js

metadata.name: Cacography #173
metadata.description:
Further explorations on textures with a hand drawn style. This time in combination with flow fields.

In the live view, the sketch will take up the entire browser window.
After resizing your browser window to a custom size, refresh the page or hit the F key. The sketch will then assume the new dimensions.
  
Press the B key to toggle borderless mode.

Due to the large amount of lines that have to be drawn this can take a couple of seconds.
Sorry, not sorry, if your browser explodes XD

metadata.description:
As New Dawn Fades it was time to release this project. It's about division and why not reference this band I listened when I was young...

metadata.name: Trasiedoc #54
metadata.description:
Behind every generative art project is a code. This code is sometimes a masterpiece but most viewers do not see it.

With the Trasiedoc project I wanted to highlight the hidden face of generative art, the code, by literally integrating the code of my biggest project to date (Dencity) in each output of the Trasiedoc project.

Margins can be hidden by pressing "x" in live mode (and optionally press "p" to see if anything happens).

Made with ❤️, code, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Two Point Zero #132
metadata.description:
This project is a commemorative generative art project for fxhash, where I started my journey in collecting and minting art on the blockchain. What a ride it has been! This is a collab project developed with my daughter (14) as part of her STEM Fair Project. The “stacked ellipses” function was created and written by her, and will be the sole output for her project. We plan to set up a large monitor at her event and offer phyical prints on site :). She’s an amazing and beautiful human; I can't wait to see her make more art! I hope you enjoy them as much as we’ve enjoyed making this project. This artwork prints both the generative hash and the iteration number on the canvas when it’s minted.

6000x8000 res

Press S to save canvas as jpg.
Preas P to save canvas as png.

Created with p5.js and a very patient and creative daughter. ❤

metadata.name: Ten (reissue) #55
metadata.description:
This is a reissue of "Ten". Because of a security policy update on fxhash and a mistake on my part (loading p5.js externally), the original project doesn't load anymore in the live view.  "Ten (reissue)" has exactly the same code, but with the fix (which doesn't influence the visuals).

Original project: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/13173

--

Ten colors, ten palettes, ten styles. "Ten" is a collection of mathematical illustrations, combining techniques I have explored in past projects with my latest experiments.

Press [s] to save the image in 4096x4096 resolution.

By Roni Block (@BlockRoni)
Made with p5.js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Erg #32
metadata.description:
Erg - derived from the Arabic word ʿarq (عرق), meaning "dune field”.

A collaboration between Ballzerino and Rich Poole, Erg is a compact generative series evolved from Ballzerino’s original work “Dune”.

100% of mint proceeds and royalties will be donated to TezQuakeAid

metadata.name: White Mountain Winter #102
metadata.description:
White Mountain Winter is collaboration between myself and the machine to describe scenes that are real, or were. Yet perhaps now foreign, or out of time, or far away. I provide the seed of a dream I remember, and trust the machine to help make it real again.

I grew up in a town much like some of these, homes dispersed throughout the valley beneath the shadows of the mountains rising around. This is a tribute to the memory of wintertime in that place; bleak, cold, grey, with the light seemingly always fading. Yet at the same time, the feeling of calm, solace, peace resonating through. Exposed to the mountain elements, yet protected by them. A delicate arrangement, but essential.

The seed of magic I remember is present in the experience of falling snow at dusk. Large flakes tumbling down and blanketing everything, no end in sight. The most striking thing is the silence. The fallen snow absorbing all distraction, insisting that your focus be sharpened to a singularity; right there, right then.

---
- Best rendered in Chrome browser (best performance, & canvas blur - please be patient :)
- Made with p5js
- Press "s" to save png

This work is the second in the ridge series. While using the same base algorithm this work is about exploring landscapes using a much more dark and desolate imagery.

It was designed to be experienced in fullscreen in live mode.
Press "s" to save a screenshot.

Dutch auction (14/11/8), updating every 5min.

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #10
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‘Organic Matr’ (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


—— 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter’s wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‘scale’ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.
